Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[But the earlier report (see ProMED-mail 20141010.2851912) said, "consignment of beef to be withdrawn from the market because it may be contaminated with anthrax. " Note "may" not "is". According to the OIE report (see ProMED-mail 20141001.2822945) the original outbreak on the Slovak farm started on or about 27 Sep 2014, and confirmed on 29 Sep 2014. 2 cattle from the Slovak farm were sold and slaughtered on 19 Sep 2014 in Poland when nothing abnormal was noted; anthrax was diagnosed on this Slovak farm a week later. The Dutch authorities were demonstrating an abundance of caution. - Mod.MHJ]
